question: What is the average tenure of employees in different departments?

question: What are the survival chances of allgery Shellfish (substance)?
answers:
SELECT DISTINCT p.GENDER, COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) as total_patients, 
COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN a.DESCRIPTION = 'Shellfish (substance)' THEN p.Id ELSE NULL END) as allergy_patients, 
COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN a.DESCRIPTION = 'Shellfish (substance)' THEN p.Id ELSE NULL END) * 1.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) as survival_chance
FROM patients p 
LEFT JOIN allergies a ON a.PATIENT = p.Id 
WHERE a.DESCRIPTION = 'Shellfish (substance)' 
GROUP BY p.GENDER;

question: What is the successrate of medication 24 HR Metformin hydrochloride 500 MG Extended Release Oral Tablet?

    COUNT(CASE WHEN m.DESCRIPTION = '24 HR Metformin hydrochloride 500 MG Extended Release Oral Tablet' AND p.HEALTHCARE_EXPENSES > 0 THEN 1 END) / 
    COUNT(CASE WHEN m.DESCRIPTION = '24 HR Metformin hydrochloride 500 MG Extended Release Oral Tablet' THEN 1 END) AS success_rate
FROM 
    medications m 
    LEFT JOIN patients p ON m.PATIENT = p.Id 
WHERE 
    m.DESCRIPTION = '24 HR Metformin hydrochloride 500 MG Extended Release Oral Tablet';

question: What are the survival chances of allgery Allergy to substance (finding)?
answers:
SELECT 
    a.description, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT p.birthdate) AS total_patients, 
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN p.deathdate IS NOT NULL THEN p.birthdate ELSE NULL END) AS deceased_patients, 
    ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN p.deathdate IS NOT NULL THEN p.birthdate ELSE NULL END) * 1.0 / COUNT(DISTINCT p.birthdate) * 100, 2) AS survival_rate
FROM 
    patients p 
    LEFT JOIN allergies a ON a.patient = p.id 
WHERE 
    a.description = 'Allergy to substance (finding)'
GROUP BY 
    a.description;

What are the survival chances of allgery House dust mite (organism)?

SELECT DISTINCT p.GENDER, COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) as total_patients, 
COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN a.DESCRIPTION = 'House dust mite (organism)' THEN p.Id ELSE NULL END) as affected_patients, 
ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN a.DESCRIPTION = 'House dust mite (organism)' THEN p.Id ELSE NULL END) / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) * 100, 2) as survival_chance

LEFT JOIN allergies a ON a.PATIENT = p.Id

GROUP BY p.GENDER;

question: What is the total number of months being a member for the payer with ID a735bf55-83e9-331a-899d-a82a60b9f60c?
answers:
SELECT SUM(m.member_months) 
FROM (SELECT payer_id, SUM(member_months) as member_months 
      FROM (SELECT p.id, p.name, e.payer, EXTRACT(YEAR FROM AGE(e.stop, e.start)) * 12 + EXTRACT(MONTH FROM AGE(e.stop, e.start)) - EXTRACT(MONTH FROM e.start) + 1 as member_months 
             FROM encounters e 
             WHERE e.payer = 'a735bf55-83e9-331a-899d-a82a60b9f60c') t 
      GROUP BY payer_id) m;

question: What is the total number of months being a member for the payer with ID e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496?
answers:
SELECT SUM(m.member_months) 
FROM (SELECT payer_id, SUM(member_months) as member_months 
      FROM (SELECT payer_id, DATEDIFF(COALESCE(end_date, CURRENT_DATE), start_date) / 30 as member_months 
            FROM payer_transitions 
            WHERE payer_id = 'e03e23c9-4df1-3eb6-a62d-f70f02301496' 
            GROUP BY payer_id) as subquery) as subquery;

    COUNT(CASE WHEN m.DESCRIPTION = 'NDA020800 0.3 ML Epinephrine 1 MG/ML Auto-Injector' AND m.REASONCODE IS NULL THEN 1 END) AS success_count,
    COUNT(*) AS total_count,
    ROUND(COUNT(CASE WHEN m.DESCRIPTION = 'NDA020800 0.3 ML Epinephrine 1 MG/ML Auto-Injector' AND m.REASONCODE IS NULL THEN 1 END) / COUNT(*) * 100, 2) AS success_rate
FROM 
    medications m
WHERE 
    m.DESCRIPTION = 'NDA020800 0.3 ML Epinephrine 1 MG/ML Auto-Injector';

question: What are the survival chances of allgery House dust mite (organism)?
answers:
SELECT DISTINCT p.GENDER, COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) AS total_patients, 
COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN a.DESCRIPTION = 'House dust mite (organism)' THEN p.Id ELSE NULL END) AS affected_patients, 
ROUND(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN a.DESCRIPTION = 'House dust mite (organism)' THEN p.Id ELSE NULL END) / COUNT(DISTINCT p.Id) * 100, 2) AS survival_chance
FROM patients p 
LEFT JOIN allergies a ON a.PATIENT = p.Id 
WHERE a.DESCRIPTION = 'House dust mite (organism)' 
GROUP BY p.GENDER;

      FROM (SELECT payer_id, EXTRACT(YEAR FROM age(end_date, start_date)) * 12 + EXTRACT(MONTH FROM age(end_date, start_date)) as member_months
